  notes:
    - "Wave 678 (st3466): __iter__, __next__, __len__ dict-presence checks for struct.Struct."
    - "Theme: __iter__/__next__/__len__ dict-presence (iter(x), next(x), len(x))."
    - "All values False — hashlib/uuid/struct/socket types do not implement iterator or sizing protocols."
    - "struct.Struct is a C-level type (_struct.Struct); it does not define __iter__, __next__, or __len__ in its own __dict__."
    - "struct.Struct instances represent compiled format strings — they are binary format descriptors and do not implement iterator or sizing protocols."
    - "All values are False — struct.Struct has no iter/next/len defined in its own __dict__."
    - "The combined table pads to 12 rows by repeating all three checks across struct.Struct."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

